node.text:
Everyone, meet Rockee! ❤️ ⠀
Do you believe things happen for a reason?⠀
⠀
A few months ago, I found a pregnant stray cat that looked very skinny, so I decided to turn it into a daily ritual to bring her food and snuggles. Since I was already feeding 4 cats, I was thinking one more won’t hurt. And this one really looked like it needed some help. ⠀
⠀
I went there for about one month and found her waiting for me every single day. After a few weeks she started to gain weight and looked a lot healthier. And my, how happy she was to get her daily cuddles! ⠀
⠀
One morning I looked for her and couldn’t find her, that must have been the day she gave birth. I figured my job here was done, thinking she would probably take some weeks until revealing her kittens to me. And finally, a few weeks ago I passed by that area with my friend and saw her. I stopped and bent down to pet her and said to my friend “I still haven’t seen her kittens, I wish I could finally see them” when my friend pointed at the wooden deck right behind me. “You mean those kittens?“ ⠀
⠀
I turned around and saw two very cute kittens. They were greyish-brown colored with beautiful markings just like their mommy. Shortly after I noticed a third kitten that looked very different from the others. Its fur was black and white and it didn’t have any remarkable fur patterns. The next thing I noticed was that it was missing one arm. ⠀
⠀
Only a few days later I heard a guy talking about a three legged kitten. Of course, I immediately knew which kitten he was referring to. A small local organization was going to take it to a shelter, because its leg got infected. I think the words were something like „nobody will adopt a three legged kitten“. It was one of these moments where logic fails and you feel like you’re guided by an invisible hand that shows you the way. You have no idea what you’re doing or why you’re doing it, but it feels right. I call it intuition. And all you can do is trust in it, trust that you’re exactly in the right place at the right time doing the right thing. ⠀
⠀
Welcome to your forever home, Rockee. I believe you’re here for a reason and I can’t wait to find out what you’re going to teach us. ❤️

node.text:
Dear friends, so happy to tell you that we have a new familee member: Please meet little miss Dumpling 🦔🥟❤️⠀
⠀
A few weeks ago I decided to rescue another little hedgehog after I received a message from a lovely girl named Gigi (@gigiknightley) who had read Herbee’s rescue story. Turns out she had the same allergic problems as Cathy (Herbee’s previous owner) and therefore heavy-heartedly decided to give her hedgehog away and asked me for help 😔💔⠀
⠀
Long story short: I decided to adopt Dumpling, who has been with me for two weeks now and I can already tell she’s such a sweetheart. She’s two years old and had two previous owners already. Gigi mentioned that it’s possible that she was abused by her first owner because apparently she had burn marks on her quills. For that reason Dumpling was really shy and huffed quite a lot when I first got to know her, but she warmed up to me very quickly. With a lot of patience and care Gigi must have managed to let her build up trust to people again 🦔❤️‍🩹 ⠀
⠀
You know how they say “good things come in three’s” right? So, little miss Dumpling, I am so happy to give you your third, but final and forever home as our third hedgehog in the Pokee Familee! ❤️⠀
⠀
PS. You might have noticed that the name Dumpling doesn’t exactly match our “ee” name tradition. And even though “Dumpee” isn’t exactly the cutest name on the planet, there’s one thing about her that really makes this nickname the perfect match. Telling you more in today’s story - let us know in the comments what you think!! 🦔🦔🦔
